The paper deals with the formation and analysis of social networks, which falls under the scope of social networks and information science. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with optimization problems, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with preference aggregation, which could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper deals with influence maximization, which could be categorized under cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks).
